<br>
Premise:  Warriors have been experiencing a dramatic and steady decrease in relative power, as many other classes have been coddled and upgraded, and the class is fading into a role of second or 3rd tier melee, their use being exclusive only on raids where only thier most powerful (yet 2 expansions old) features are necessary.<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Let me state unequivocally that yes, the discipline of defensive (and to another degree the discipline of evasive when selected correctly) are very powerful tools in the arsenal of a warrior.  This solidifies their need on raids on &quot;high melee&quot; mobs.  Let me also state that these disciplines are 2 expansions old, and weren't nearly as useful when they were fresh as they were in Velious (and to a MUCH lesser degree in most of Luclin).<br>
<br>
When the preposterous notion of &quot;melee balncing&quot; came out, a paraphrased version of the message given to warriors was...<br>
<br>
&quot;You guys have the highest AC and Hitpoints, and decent melee, therefore, you will experience no changes and will be the standard by which we judge other classes&quot;.<br>
<br>
Well, it turns out that this wasn't necessarily true, it would be true under certain conditions, such as...<br>
<br>
...When naked, you have the best AC/HP of any other class.<br>
<br>
...When all equipped in class specific Velious quest armor with epics, you have the best AC/HP of any other class<br>
<br>
What we've learned is that AC is for @#%$, and therefore, unless you're talking about low level mobs, even similarly equipped toons of the same level will all receive the same benefit from AC, which seems to cap out around 1250ish.   There is simply no melee class who cannot fairly easily get to the &quot;soft cap&quot; which sort of deflates the 'you have the highest AC' argument to meaningless.   <br>
<br>
We've also learned that the 2 plate wearing hybrid classes (those who should suffer SOME penalty to melee for their utility, escapability, class specific features, spells, etc.) have FAR easier access to (and this is key, LIMITED ACCESS) equipment which is dramatically better than that which is available to warriors.   By this, I mean that the rate of VI limited Pal/SK only equipment, particularly in Luclin is fairly dramatic.   Compound that with the fact that there's very little, to nothing in the way of &quot;War only&quot; shiz around in any of the slots that represents any improvement of OUR class (Whereas flowing thought abounds).  <br>
<br>
Add to this, the stuff that DOES represent a huge increase in warrior usable equipment normally makes warriors feel like an ass taking because it makes the most sense being on another toon.  Examples of this are particularly available in light of things such as the belt from the restless burrower, which includes +100mana, +15 Wis, and +15 Int, while the things of importance to the warrior are the +Sta, and the +100hp).  What happens is that the upgrade path for warriors now takes SIGNIFICANTLY longer than it does for others, in particular for conscientious warriors who feel bad about wasting stats on them such as mana/wis and int.   <br>
<br>
This is NOT, nor should it ever be construed as an attack on other melee classes, or as a desire to see nerfage, but let's get realistic now.  I'm about to touch on AA skills.<br>
<br>
Warriors were alone in the &quot;eye candy&quot; department (crits, crippling blows), this was given to us many moons ago as a way of &quot;balancing&quot; us, as we were relatively weak (in a similar position as to where we are now in my estimation).   From time to time a big crippling blow made a difference, but the cool thing was we were the only ones, what we did made people look.  Now, it's nothing but spam.  Everyone who wants to get it can get it.  But this is compounded by the fact that we're still getting minimal damage on these, and they're more of an annoyance than anything else.   In the advent of 19,000 point critical manaburns, a 500 point crippling blow is nothing but /yawn.   This was our exclusive domain and now clerics can even get critical blasts if they spend their points like this.<br>
<br>
Rangers:  Went from average melee with some utility spells to GODS with AM3, and Endless Quiver.   I absolutely LOVE that for them, they should have been archery masters all along, but at a cost, as is the philosophy behind &quot;balance&quot;.  When a ranger can hit the same AC and 6k+ hp buffed, with CS3 and CA 3, they can be and are formidable tanks as well.   There seems to be no real tradeoff, no balance.<br>
<br>
Paladins:  While they SHOULD be the masters against undead, Slay Undead has become simply a way of taking a class that SHOULD suffer a penalty to melee and made them GODS (again, 5,000 point critical hits in melee with all of the utility allotted to Paladins while warriors still pound away at similar con mobs for 50, 60, 70 points, or 290ish max with primal seems totally out of line).  Free horses, and an abundance of available equipment at relatively low cost, along with no need to hold back on NON-Int/Wis/Mana items which also have +Sta, and +100hp, because they're not limited seems wrong to me.<br>
<br>
Shadowknights:  Well, they haven't gotten the MASSIVE aa increases that others have gotten, yet, they can STILL acheive the same levels of AC/HP as warriors, and STILL out taunt warriors, making them PREFERRED tanks on certain mobs over warriors and the ONE job that we're supposed to have.<br>
<br>
In aa skills, warriors will follow the same road EVERY TIME.   3 in Run 3, 3 in something else (usually regen) 3 in Natural Durability, Slap Area Taunt (Because we need to have a taunt that works!) then back for Combat Stability and Combat Agility.  After that, nothing truly makes a warrior THAT much more powerful, or THAT much more capable of performing their jobs.   This doesn't mention that Natural Durability, Combat Stability and Combat Agility can ALL be used by everyone else.   We have ONE class skill that we use regularly, AE taunt.  But wait a second, AE taunt wasn't designed nor was it supposed to be used as nothing more than a guaranteed taunt buttin, but this is what it has become because VI has not been able to give us RELIABLE taunt.   They didn't have the foresight to have as a CLASS skill *increased agitation* which modified the effectiveness of taunt, the ONLY thing we're good for.   <br>
<br>
This leads to basic exp grouping!   VI revamps a dungeon that they may as well have called &quot;The temple of Hybrid Heaven&quot;, as they completely disabled taunt, making us worthless in the zone.  Fine, they fixed it after the nightmares, but it still doesn't alter the fact that their intentions became known, which is that they feel that warriors needing to tank exp mobs is undesirable.<br>
<br>
With the ability of everyone who can wield a weapon to train in CS3 and CA3, warriors' place as tanks has been relegated to zilch.  Why?  Well, because we really do suck at gaining aggro, whereas all hybrids can gain it FAR easier and more reliably than we can if they assert themselves, therfore we have no real place in an exp group.   <br>
<br>
I've never seen a time in EQ where warriors were forced to solo so much because their group desirablity has gone from one extreme to the other.   While with the right equipment, we CAN solo, we're nowhere near the capability of repeatedly soloing like a SU Paladin, or an arrow kiting ranger.  We're STRICT melee, and should in my mind have some advantages to that, such as being BETTER, not a little, but a LOT better than non strict melees, not significantly WORSE based on mob choice.  <br>
<br>
My recommendations for improving the current pathetic state of warriors:<br>
<br>
1. Itemization in Luclin/PoP (and this is true in a lot of Velious)<br>
<br>
Make some warrior only stuff, or at least some -Int/-Wis/-Mana +HP, +Sta stuff for plate classes so that there's a logical idea that this should go to a warrior.  Jesus, all you'd have to do is have an item with +100 hp which has a negative mana/tick effect (i.e. Escaping thought).   We're damn sick of being conscientious and forking over the stuff that best suits someone else, yet when stuff best suits US, it also well suits everyone else.<br>
<br>
Also, WTF is wrong with making some spiked plate boots that increase kick damage, or proc?   We HAVE a button for kick, but regardless of our skill, we cannot increase our melee damage on kick.<br>
<br>
2. AA Skills:  Make them not suck ass.   I've got some ideas:<br>
<br>
- Increased Agitation:  Make taunt friggin WORK so we don't have to be forced to used a decent situational skill (taunting all mobs in an area) into &quot;The only way to reliably taunt&quot;.<br>
<br>
- Decapitate:  I don't know why the hell we don't get the ability to decapitate when using 2hs, similar to rogues use of asassinate, on mobs of similar size or smaller than us.<br>
<br>
- When I was level 54, Mightystrike was the coolest thing ever.   Now that I'm 60 with aa skills, I see it as a waste of time and energy, and dangerous because it disables my disciplines for so long, even though it's not overpowered.   Why not an AA skill which acheives a similar effect for a longer period of time?   I mean, come on, manaburn is ok, but having an &quot;always crit/Crip&quot; for 30 seconds even while using discs is?   I'm a friggin WARLORD, and I should be able to get fire in my eyes and go on a frenzied rampage laying devastation from time to time without sacrificing my ability to go defensive for the next hour.   Make a mightystrike type aa class skill.   It certainly wouldn't take anything away from anyone else, but would sure make MY experience more fun.<br>
<br>
Finally, in summary:<br>
<br>
Don't fuggin upgrade EVERYONE but warriors, give out items that best serve someone else, but then not protect us on items, give out AA skills that are meaningful to everyone BUT us, and expect silence, that's B.S. and shouldn't be tolerated.   <br>
<br>
And if my snarepoop ever gets nerfed...I cannot be held responsible for my actions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukbern.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kbern</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 10:51:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> Very well thought out post.  Not sure what to say.  Alot of it makes sense. <p><img src="http://scarecrow.clickhere2.net/images/oaksiggy_new1.gif" border=0></a><br><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=253834">Saurakk Rex</a>
